      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARISPHERE (3) progressed nicely last time out at the second run of the campaign and finished just 1.5 lengths from the winner in second over 1000m at Sunshine Coast. Worth noting winning rider Emily Lang goes aboard. Looks well placed so expect another big run. MUSCHIALLI (2) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1200m at Doomben, beaten 3.5 lengths into sixth. This easier than recent outings and has the class to find the winners' list. JOY A PLENTY (4) has scored at her last two starts, most recently by 0.8 lengths over 1100m at Ipswich. That continued the good form this campaign, with three wins and two minor placings from six starts. Should be in the finish. COUNT NICHOLAS (8) rolled forward last time out and boxed on to finish a nose from the winner in second at Gold Coast Poly over 1150m. Bella Youngberry who has scored on him three times retains the mount. Worth including in calculations.",
